<BaseLayout title="About — Return to Breath" description="About Return to Breath — the project, the people, the intent." lang="en">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 pt-32 pb-24">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 leading-tight mb-10">About.</h1>
    <div class="space-y-6 text-[17px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed">
      <p>This is an essential project.</p>
      <p>The number of adults whose nervous systems are running too hot is no longer a fringe statistic. It is the baseline state of working life in most developed economies. Cognitive load is at historic highs. Sleep is collapsing. Anxiety is rising across every age cohort. The structures that used to provide coherence — stable careers, predictable institutions, intelligible economies, durable identities — are dissolving faster than most people can adapt to.</p>
      <p>The work here is the response to that. To put one practical instrument — the breath — into the hands of people who need it, without any of the things that would normally come with a wellness brand: no community, no streaks, no gamification, no infinite optimization.</p>
      <p>A book. A weekly letter. The Return app. The intent is that more people can live more coherently in a destabilizing time. That is the whole purpose.</p>
    </div>
    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-12" />
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-6">Christoph Kneip</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6 text-[17px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed">
      <p>Author of <em class="text-slate-200">Return to Breath</em>. Roughly a decade as head of procurement at a multinational. Sustained student of contemplative practice — particularly the geometric and harmonic frameworks of Robert Edward Grant. Based in Zürich, Switzerland.</p>
    </div>
    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-12" />
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-6">Rickard Strongert · Contributor</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6 text-[17px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed">
      <p>Post-identity coach based in Marbella, Spain. Works with people at the threshold between an identity that no longer fits and the next form that has not yet arrived.</p>
    </div>
    <hr class="border-slate-800 my-12" />
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-50 mb-6">Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed">For correspondence: <a href="mailto:info@returnapp.org" class="text-sapphire-400 hover:text-sapphire-300 transition-colors">info@returnapp.org</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
